93e0d7a8-1ece-44fd-b559-115a7ada88c9.306f07a1-ff7f-4d5d-8002-034fc42e370a.description=
This is an operation that does nothing. It can be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.
93e0d7a8-1ece-44fd-b559-115a7ada88c9.5bd76140-08be-462d-83c9-a9673c622c5c.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

93e0d7a8-1ece-44fd-b559-115a7ada88c9.84245aea-879a-4375-b713-8cc99bb877b7.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

93e0d7a8-1ece-44fd-b559-115a7ada88c9.c218c4de-0c2c-4863-a24f-fc02e076a659.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

93e0d7a8-1ece-44fd-b559-115a7ada88c9.description=
Build Fixed IP Customization Specification XML.

Inputs Parameters\:

 customSpecXml - User provided customization specification
 customSpecType - Type of the customization specification type i.e. Linux or Windows
 osType - OS type specified by the user.
 ipAddress - IP Address
 subnetMask - Subnet Mask
 gatewayIpList - List of gateway IP address
 dnsServerIpList - List of DNS server IP address

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.

Output\:
customizationSpecXml - Customization Specification XML with Fixed IP.
flow.name: vCenter Build Fixed IP CustomSpec XML
